04/12/2007
SKOPJE, Macedonia -- UN special envoy in the name dispute between Macedonia and Greece, Matthew Nimetz, was in Skopje on Monday (December 3rd) to hear the government's response to his proposal aimed at definitively resolving the matter. After meetings with President Branko Crvenkovski, Prime Minister Nikola Gruevski, Foreign Minister Antonio Milososki and other officials, Nimetz said there is a determination to settle the dispute and he expressed satisfaction with his visit to Skopje, describing it as "significant". He is due to visit Athens on Wednesday. (Vecer, Utrinski Vesnik - 04/12/07; Makfax, ERT, MIA, MRT, A1, Kanal 77, Xinhua, AP - 03/12/07)
